---
// Print-optimized case study layout for "The Perfumers"
---
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>The Perfumers — Case Study</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600&family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        :root {
            --black: #0a0a0a;
            --white: #ffffff;
            --gray-100: #f5f5f5;
            --gray-200: #eeeeee;
            --gray-400: #999999;
            --gray-600: #666666;
            --gray-800: #333333;
        }

        @page {
            size: A4;
            margin: 0;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
            color: var(--black);
            background-color: var(--white);
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;
            print-color-adjust: exact;
        }

        .page {
            width: 210mm;
            min-height: 297mm;
            padding: 20mm;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background: white;
            box-sizing: border-box;
            page-break-after: always;
            position: relative;
        }

        /* Typography */
        h1, h2, h3, h4, .serif {
            font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
            font-weight: 400;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 52px;
            line-height: 1.1;
            letter-spacing: -0.02em;
            margin: 0 0 16px 0;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 32px;
            line-height: 1.2;
            margin: 0 0 24px 0;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--black);
            padding-bottom: 8px;
        }

        .tagline {
            font-size: 20px;
            color: var(--gray-600);
            font-style: italic;
            margin-top: 0;
            margin-bottom: 40px;
        }

        .meta-label {
            font-size: 9px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.15em;
            color: var(--gray-400);
            margin-bottom: 4px;
        }

        .meta-value {
            font-size: 11px;
            font-weight: 500;
            color: var(--black);
        }

        p {
            font-size: 14px;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: var(--gray-800);
            font-weight: 300;
            margin-bottom: 24px;
        }

        .pullquote {
            font-size: 28px;
            line-height: 1.3;
            font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
            color: var(--black);
            margin: 60px 0;
            padding-left: 20px;
            border-left: 2px solid var(--black);
        }

        /* Layout Grids */
        .grid-2 {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            gap: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 40px;
        }

        .grid-3 {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
            gap: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 40px;
        }

        .grid-4 {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
            gap: 20px;
            border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
            padding-top: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 40px;
        }

        .block-card {
            background-color: var(--gray-100);
            padding: 24px;
        }

        /* Images */
        .img-hero {
            width: 100%;
            height: 120mm;
            object-fit: cover;
            margin-bottom: 40px;
        }

        .img-gallery {
            width: 100%;
            aspect-ratio: 4/3;
            object-fit: cover;
            background-color: var(--gray-200);
        }
        
        .img-full {
             width: 100%;
             height: auto;
             max-height: 110mm;
             object-fit: cover;
             margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        .footer {
            position: absolute;
            bottom: 20mm;
            left: 20mm;
            right: 20mm;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            font-size: 9px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.2em;
            color: var(--gray-400);
            border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
            padding-top: 10px;
        }

        .page-break {
            page-break-before: always;
        }
        
        /* Dark Page Variant */
        .page.dark {
            background-color: var(--black);
            color: var(--white);
        }
        .page.dark h1, .page.dark h2, .page.dark .meta-value, .page.dark .pullquote {
            color: var(--white);
        }
        .page.dark p {
            color: #cccccc;
        }
        .page.dark .meta-label, .page.dark .tagline {
            color: #888888;
        }
        .page.dark h2 {
            border-bottom-color: #333333;
        }
        .page.dark .block-card {
            background-color: #1a1a1a;
        }
        .page.dark .footer {
            border-top-color: #333333;
        }

        .list-item {
            display: flex;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
        }
        .list-bullet {
            width: 20px;
            font-weight: 600;
        }
        
        strong {
            font-weight: 500;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- PAGE 1: Cover & Metas -->
    <div class="page">
        <h1 class="serif">The Perfumers</h1>
        <p class="tagline">The creation of your story scent.</p>
        
        <img src="/projects/kht-the-perfumers/1_the_perfumers_banner.jpg" class="img-hero" alt="The Perfumers Hero">

        <div class="grid-4">
            <div>
                <div class="meta-label">Client</div>
                <div class="meta-value">Khaltat</div>
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="meta-label">Project Type</div>
                <div class="meta-value">360 Campaign</div>
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="meta-label">Region</div>
                <div class="meta-value">UAE</div>
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="meta-label">Duration</div>
                <div class="meta-value">3 Months</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="meta-label" style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Executive Summary</div>
            <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8;">
                A UAE-wide contest campaign that invited perfume enthusiasts to become “perfumers” by mixing and naming their own custom scent using a guided mixing kit—supported by retail VM/installations, a landing page, and multiple campaign videos.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="footer">
            <span>Case Study</span>
            <span>Rima Alshoufi — Creative Director</span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- PAGE 2: Problem, Insight, Strategy -->
    <div class="page dark">
        <h2>The Strategic Pivot</h2>
        
        <div class="grid-3" style="margin-top: 40px;">
            <div class="block-card">
                <div class="meta-label" style="margin-bottom: 16px;">The Challenge</div>
                <p>Build a campaign that doesn’t just advertise perfume—but gets people to create perfume. The goal was to make the highly technical, complex craft of perfume mixing accessible and engaging enough to trigger user-generated content (UGC), while maintaining momentum through contest cycles and evaluations.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="block-card">
                <div class="meta-label" style="margin-bottom: 16px;">The Insight</div>
                <p>Gen Z and younger audiences deeply desire self-expression and social proof through making something original. While perfumery is often perceived as an exclusive, closed-off craft, positioning it as a "creator tool" bridges the gap between premium luxury and modern maker culture.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="block-card">
                <div class="meta-label" style="margin-bottom: 16px;">The Big Idea</div>
                <p><strong style="color: white; font-size: 16px; display: block; margin-bottom: 8px;">Blending as Storytelling</strong>We invited customers to unleash their creativity and become the masterminds behind their own scent creation. Instead of passive consumption, participants blend, name, and share their signature fragrance, transforming into a vibrant maker community.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="pullquote">
            "Not just advertising perfume—getting people to create it."
        </div>

        <div class="footer">
            <span>The Perfumers</span>
            <span>Page 02</span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- PAGE 3: Execution Images -->
    <div class="page">
        <h2>The Execution ecosystem</h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 40px;">The campaign rolled out as a 360-experience, blending physical material with retail integration and digital scale.</p>

        <img src="/projects/kht-the-perfumers/final_round.jpg" class="img-full" alt="Final Round Execution">

        <div class="grid-2">
            <img src="/projects/kht-the-perfumers/2_the_perfumers_banner.jpg" class="img-gallery" alt="Campaign Banner">
            <img src="/projects/kht-the-perfumers/store_photo.jpg" class="img-gallery" alt="Retail Execution" style="object-position: top;">
        </div>

        <div class="footer">
            <span>The Perfumers</span>
            <span>Page 03</span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- PAGE 4: Mechanics and Outcomes -->
    <div class="page page-break">
        <h2 style="margin-bottom: 40px;">Outcomes & Mechanics</h2>
        
        <div class="grid-2">
            <div>
                <div class="meta-label" style="margin-bottom: 16px;">The Mechanics</div>
                <div class="list-item">
                    <div class="list-bullet">01</div>
                    <p><strong>The Mixing Kit.</strong> Designed as a portable “small laboratory” for experimentation and structured guidance.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="list-item">
                    <div class="list-bullet">02</div>
                    <p><strong>Retail Integration.</strong> Window executions, small display units, and an in-store photo backdrop for immediate sharing.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="list-item">
                    <div class="list-bullet">03</div>
                    <p><strong>Digital Pipeline.</strong> Registration via landing page with QR codes linking to mixing tutorials and inspiration.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="list-item">
                    <div class="list-bullet">04</div>
                    <p><strong>The Contest Loop.</strong> Participants submit their mixes, stories, and share socially before a final jury evaluation.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="block-card">
                <div class="meta-label" style="margin-bottom: 16px;">Confirmed Outcomes</div>
                <h3 style="font-size: 48px; margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-weight: 300;">600+</h3>
                <p style="font-weight: 500; font-size: 16px; margin-bottom: 40px;">Active participants successfully mixed their own unique scents.</p>
                
                <h3 style="font-size: 32px; margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-weight: 300;">Virality</h3>
                <p style="font-weight: 500; font-size: 16px; margin-bottom: 0;">Organic spread achieved on TikTok and Instagram through campaign hashtags and UGC.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div style="margin-top: 60px; padding-top: 20px; border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-200);">
            <div class="meta-label">Creative Direction</div>
            <p><strong>Role:</strong> Concept, naming, storytelling, competition design, and overall creative direction.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="footer">
            <span>The Perfumers</span>
            <span>Page 04</span>
        </div>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
